fnTrapCpuThreshold.desc: Indicates that the CPU usage has exceeded the configured threshold.

fnTrapMemThreshold.desc: Indicates memory usage has exceeded the configured threshold.

fnTrapLogDiskThreshold.desc: Log disk usage has exceeded the configured threshold. Only availableon devices with log disks.

fnTrapTempHigh.desc: A temperature sensor on the device has exceeded its threshold.Not all devices have thermal sensors. See manual for specifications.

fnTrapVoltageOutOfRange.desc: Power levels have fluctuated outside of normal levels. Not all deviceshave voltage monitoring instrumentation. See manual for specifications.

fnTrapPowerSupplyFailure.desc: Power supply failure detected. Not available on all models. Availableon some devices which support redundant power supplies. See manualfor specifications.

fnTrapIpChange.desc: Indicates that the IP address of the specified interface has been changed.

fnTrapTest.desc: Trap sent for diagnostic purposes by an administrator.

fgTrapVpnTunUp.desc: Indicates that the specified VPN tunnel has been brought up.

fgTrapVpnTunDown.desc: The specified VPN tunnel has been brought down.

fgTrapHaSwitch.desc: The specified cluster member has transitioned from a slave role to a master role.

fgTrapHaStateChange.desc: Trap being sent when the HA clustermember changes its state

fgTrapHaHBFail.desc: The heartbeat device failure count has exceeded the configured threshold.

fgTrapHaMemberDown.desc: The specified device (by serial number) is moving to a down state.

fgTrapHaMemberUp.desc: A new cluster member has joined the cluster.

fgTrapIpsSignature.desc: An IPS signature has been triggered

fgTrapIpsAnomaly.desc: An IPS anomaly has been detected

fgTrapIpsPkgUpdate.desc: The IPS signature database has been updated

fgTrapIpsFailOpen.desc: The IPS network buffer is full

fgTrapAvVirus.desc: A virus has been detected by the anti-virus engine

fgTrapAvOversize.desc: An over-sized file has been detected by the anti-virus engine

fgTrapAvPattern.desc: The anti-virus engine has blocked a file because it matched a configured pattern

fgTrapAvFragmented.desc: The anti-virus engine has detected a fragmented file

fgTrapAvEnterConserve.desc: The anti-virus engine has entered conservation mode due to low memory conditions

fgTrapAvBypass.desc: The anti-virus engine has been bypassed due to conservation mode

fgTrapAvOversizePass.desc: An over-sized file has been detected,but has been passed due to configuration

fgTrapAvOversizeBlock.desc: An over-sized file has been detectedand has been blocked

fgTrapFazDisconnect.desc: The device has been disconnected from the FortiAnalyzer.

fgTrapWcApUp.desc: Indicates that the specified AP is up.

fgTrapWcApDown.desc: Indicates that the specified AP is down.

fgTrapFcSwUp.desc: Indicates that the specified switch controller session is up.

fgTrapFcSwDown.desc: Indicates that the specified switch controller session is down.

fgTrapServerLoadBalanceRealServerDown.desc: One of servers in a Server Load Balance group goes down.

fgUsbportClass.syntax: INTEGER { ifc(0), audio(1), comm(2), hid(3), physical(5),image(6), printer(7), storage(8), hub(9), cdcData(10),chipSmartCard(11), contentSecurity(13), appSpec(254), vendorSpec(255)}

fgFmTrapDeployComplete.desc: Indicates when deployment of a new configuration has been completed. Used for verification by FortiManager.

fgFmTrapDeployInProgress.desc: Indicates that a configuration change was not immediate and that the change is currently in progress. Used for verification by FortiManager.

fgFmTrapConfChange.desc: The device configuration has been changed by something other than the managing FortiManager device.

fgFmTrapIfChange.desc: Trap is sent to the managing FortiManager if an interface IP is changed

fgUsbModemSignalStrength.syntax: INTEGER { sig0(0), sig1(1), sig2(2), sig3(3), sig4(4) }
